Recalls the Global Strategy and Plan of Action on Public Health, Innovation and Intellectual Property and World Health Assembly resolution 61.21 of 24 May 2008,
See World Health Organization, document WHA61/2008/REC/1. that urges Member States to support actively the wide implementation of the Global Strategy and Plan of Action and that calls upon relevant international organizations and other relevant stakeholders to give priority within their respective mandates and programmes to implementing the Global Strategy and Plan of Action, and requests Member States to take into account the recommendations of the expert review panel,
Available at https://www.who.int/publications/m/item/gspa-phi3011rev. consistent with the Global Strategy and Plan of Action, in line with national priorities;
